- A player's total salary is calculated by summing their salaries across all seasons;
- The average salary for a team is the mean salary of all players on that team across all seasons;
- The highest-paid player for each team is determined by their total salary, and only those whose total salary exceeds the team's average are selected.

- "Seasoned players" refers to players over 30 years old;
- "Drafted late" refers to players drafted in a round greater than 10;
- "Earning more than the average big bucks" refers to players with an average salary greater than $10 million.

- "1996" refers to the specific year of the season;
- "largest crowd on average" refers to the highest average attendance;
- "most attended spectacle" means the team with the highest average attendance.

- 'AL' league refers to the American League in baseball;
- 'longer-term contracts' implies a contract length greater than 3 years;
- 'drafted early' means a draft round of 1 or 2.

- 'Left-handed batters' refers to players who bat from the left side;
- 'Earning over a million dollars' refers to players with a salary greater than $1,000,000;
- 'Played more than ten games' means the team has participated in more than 10 games.

- 'American League' (AL) is one of the two leagues in Major League Baseball;
- 'combined salaries, when averaged' refers to the average salary of players on a team;
- 'golden threshold of $5,000,000' is a metaphorical way to describe a high average salary.

- 'Total salary' refers to the sum of a player's salaries across all seasons they played;
- 'Average salary of the drafting team' is the average salary of the team that initially drafted the player;
- 'Highest-paid player' is determined by the highest total salary.

- 'stars who have risen above the million-dollar mark' refers to players with a salary greater than $1,000,000;
- 'hail from the land of the free' refers to players with nationality 'USA';
- 'after the turn of the millennium' refers to seasons with a year greater than 1999.

- "American outfielders" refers to players whose nationality is 'USA' and whose position is 'Outfielder';
- "First season" is identified by season_id = 1;
- "Average salary" is calculated by taking the mean of all salaries for a specific player over the seasons.

- 'taller' refers to players with a height greater than 70 inches;
- 'well-paid' refers to players with a salary greater than $300,000;
- 'American players' refers to players with a nationality of 'USA'.

- "Free Agent" refers to a player who is not bound by a contract and is free to sign with any team;
- "Soar above the million-dollar mark" refers to an average salary greater than $2,000,000;
- "Like stars shining brightly in the economic night sky" is a metaphor for teams with high average salaries, highlighting their financial significance.

- "sown the seeds of success" refers to drafting players after 2010;
- "young talents" refers to players drafted after 2010;
- "five million mark" refers to an average salary of $5,000,000.

- "Stands atop the financial pyramid" refers to the team with the highest average salary;
- "Boasting the highest average salary" means the team with the maximum average salary;
- "Among all the players across the seasons" indicates the calculation includes all players and all seasons.
